                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-104-victim676 t18241202-104-viclabel576"></join>. I lost a pewter pot from a customer's house. I saw the prisoner at the Thames Police, where the pot was shewn to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-104-person677">
                  THOMAS 
                  GRAY
               <interp inst="t18241202-104-person677" type="surname" value="GRAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-104-person677" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-104-person677" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I apprehended the prisoner on the 17th of November, between nine and ten o'clock in the morning, at Westminster, about two miles from Mr. Gerrish's house; he was carrying a bundle, with two pint pots, marked "Three Compasses, Lambeth Marsh," and a quart pot of Mr. Gerrish's. I asked how he came by them; he said he had taken them from different person's doors, and was going to melt them down, and sell them, to get some provision for his wife - he gave me his direction in Pepper-street, but it was a false one.</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded distress.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18241202-104-verdict578" type="verdictDescription">
